<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--Break-In     05-16 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Break-In,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Chief, Former Councilman Convicted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A police chief and a former borough
councilman have been convicted of burglarizing a home while its
occupants were on vacation.
   West Pike Run Police Chief Lawrence P. Harris, 42, and former
California Councilman Walter Weld, 38, were convicted Friday of
theft, criminal conspiracy and receiving stolen property. Weld also
was convicted of a second count of receiving stolen property.
   Harris, who also is a Washington County deputy sheriff, was
suspended from his law enforcement jobs pending the outcome of his
trial.
   The charges stem from a September break-in at the home of Harry
and James Allen while they were on vacation in New Jersey.
   Key testimony came from two neighbors who said they saw the two
men carry out a television set and microwave oven from the home.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
