<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Philippines-Slaying     05-16 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Philippines-Slaying,0180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Japanese Businessman Killed During Robbery In Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four men killed a Japanese
businessman and his Filipino maid and terrorized his household for
10 hours before fleeing early today with cash and jewelry, police
said.
   Police identified the dead Japanese as Hichiro Kubota, 51, who
operated Starlight Promotions, a company which recruits Filipino
entertainers to work in Japan. He was found in his bedroom with
multiple stab wounds in the chest.
   Manila radio station DZXL said the assailants fled with about
$50,000 in cash and jewelry.
   According to police, the four men, one of whom was a former
employee, entered the home in the financial district of Makati late
Sunday night.
   They tied up Kubota, his two maids and his Filipino common-law
wife and ransacked the house. Police said Kubota's companion
telephoned police after the assailants fled this morning.
   Police found one of the maids dead in the bathroom. She was
naked and apparently had been raped, they said. Another maid and
Kubota's common-law wife suffered minor injuries, police said.
</TEXT>
