<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Lebanon-Israel     05-16 0232</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Lebanon-Israel,0238</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Palestinian Base Destroyed In Israeli Air Raid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIDON, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rocket-firing Israeli helicopter gunships
destroyed a radical Palestinian group's guerrilla base on the
outskirts of this southern port city, police reported today.
   They said three guerrillas of the Popular Front for the
Liberation of Palestine-General Command were wounded Sunday night
in the 10-minute attack by two gunships on the southern fringes of
Sidon's Ein el-Hilweh refugee camp.
   The Israeli command said the helicopters destroyed an old
building near Sidon used as a guerrilla command post, without
naming the Palestinian faction.
   An Israeli gunboat with powerful searchlights cruised in the
Mediterranean off Sidon, training the lights on the shore as the
helicopters made three runs firing rockets. The gunships also
dropped parachute flares before each run and drew anti-aircraft
fire from guerrilla positions in and around Ein el-Hilweh.
   The gunship attack was the ninth Israeli air raid on targets in
Lebanon this year. Altogether, 49 people have been killed and 75
wounded in the attacks. Three of them struck Popular Front bases.
   The group claimed responsibility for a Nov. 25 hang-glider
assault by a guerilla who flew from southeast Lebanon into northern
Israel, killing six Israelis and wounding eight before he was shot
and killed.
   The Popular Front is headed by former Syrian army captain Ahmed
Jibril. The group is based in Syria and receives financial support
from Libya.
</TEXT>
