<HEAD>Dollar Up, Stocks Near Record</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with closing figures</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar finished slightly higher Monday on the
Tokyo market, while stock prices posted a strong gain to close at a
record high.
   The dollar closed at 124.73 yen, up 0.03 yen from Friday's
close. It had opened the day at 124.83 yen and moved in a narrow
range of 124.71 yen and 124.85 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which gained 255.73 points Friday, added another
291.56 points to close at 27,759.87.
   Traders said Wall Street, which firmed Friday on news that the
U.S. producer price index rose a modest 0.4 percent, spurred the
Tokyo market's strength.
   An exchange dealer at a major commercial bank in Tokyo said the
dollar would stay in a narrow range ahead of the release of U.S.
monthly trade figures for March. The U.S. Commerce Department is
scheduled to announce the trade data in Washington Tuesday.
</TEXT>
