<2ND_LINE>PM-Britain-Rescue,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Deaf Man Uses Little Girl To Call For Help</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PENARTH, Wales (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A deaf man trying to save 10 people
stranded by a tide hoisted a little girl on his shoulders,
clambered up a cliff and used her to call for help, authorities
said.
   Alan Thomas and 6-year-old Sara Reinhardt were among 12 people
who were on a beach at the foot of a cliff Sunday when they were
stranded by a rising tide. Thomas volunteered to climb the 100-foot
cliff in this south Wales community, authorities said.
   Because he cannot hear and does not speak, he carried the girl
with him to a campground atop the bluff, where the youngster
telephoned for help. The 10 other people subsequently were picked
up by a rescue boat.
   ``Alice and Sara were very brave to climb the cliff,'' said
Dennis Fairfield of the Swansea coast guard.
</TEXT>
