<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BridgeFatal     05-16 0213</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Bridge Fatal,0220</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Driver Killed When Car Plunges Over Side of Bay Bridge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A car plunged over the side of the San
Francisco-Oakland Bay Bridge, killing the driver and marking the
first time a vehicle went off the span since it opened 51 years ago.
   The auto landed on the rocky shore of Yerba Buena Island, 130
feet below, and then rolled into the bay and sank Sunday, the
California Highway Patrol said.
   The victim's name was withheld pending notification of relatives.
   The 1978 Oldsmobile turned left after coming out of the Yerba
Buena Tunnel and drove up a metal housing for the bridge's cable
supports, investigators said.
   ``He hit the cable ramp and lofted right over the rail,'' said
Inspector Lawrence Bolger of the Navy's police department on
Treasure Island, located adjacent to Yerba Buena Island.
   ``We don't know what caused it, but the car hit an embankment,
became airborne, caught one of the cross-beams on the bridge
structure, which wound up being a ramp and propelled it over the
side into the water,'' said the patrol dispatcher in San Francisco.
   Police were still investigating the cause of the accident early
today.
   A team of San Francisco Fire Department divers searched for
other bodies but found none.
</TEXT>
