<TEXT>
   Jesse Jackson took five delegates and
Michael Dukakis four in a ``negotiated settlement'' at the Alaska
Democratic Party convention.
   Three delegates were listed as uncommitted in the bargaining
this weekend that followed Jackson's strong victories in Alaska's
precinct and district caucuses in March and April.
   Most of the voters listed as undecided in those caucuses went
Dukakis' way at the convention that ended Sunday.
   ``It was a negotiated settlement, is what it was,'' said Bob
Speed, executive director of the state Democratic Party. ``There
were two votes taken and both were very close. It had to be
negotiated from the standpoint of who got how many delegates.''
