<2ND_LINE>PM-Dukakis-Bush,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dukakis Leads Bush in Harris Poll</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michael Dukakis leads George Bush in a trial
heat between the likely presidential nominees, a Harris poll says.
   Massachusetts Gov. Dukakis, the front-runner for the Democratic
nomination, was supported by 50 percent of 2,138 likely voters
interviewed by Harris, while Vice President Bush, who has clinched
the Republican nomination, was favored by 43 percent. Seven percent
were undecided.
   Louis Harris & Associates conducted the poll in two segments,
with telephone interviews April 1-5 and May 5-10, company
spokeswoman Jill Hodge said today. Harris released the poll to
subscribers Sunday.
   Other recent polls have had Dukakis even with Bush or slightly
ahead, but analysts agree that polls conducted so far in advance of
the November election cannot be considered predictive of the
outcome.
   The margin of error for the poll was 3 percentage points.
</TEXT>
