<HEAD>Lloyd's Reduces Non-Oil Cargo Rates to Gulf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Britain's largest insurance company has cut
war-risk rates for general cargoes passing through a large area of
the southwest Persian Gulf, a Lloyd's of London spokesman said
Monday.
   The rate reduction applies to non-oil cargoes traveling in the
gulf off much of Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, Qatar, most of the United
Arab Emirates and the southern tip of Oman, said the spokesman, who
spoke on condition of anonymity. The new rates took effect last
Thursday.
   The cut reduces insurance rates for non-oil cargoes to 0.25
percent of the value of the cargo, down from 0.30 percent. The
affected area does not include the waters off Iran.
   The rate for oil cargoes for that sector of the Persian Gulf
remains unchanged at 0.375 percent, the spokesman said.
