<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-LloydWebber     05-16 0142</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Lloyd Webber,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Composer Gets Award from ASCAP</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Composer Andrew Lloyd Webber, who has three
musicals currently running on Broadway, received the first Triple
Play Award from the American Society of Composers, Author and
Publishers on Monday.
   Morton Gould, president of ASCAP, which licenses Lloyd Webber's
music in America, said it's the first such award because Lloyd
Webber is the first composer with three ``blockbuster hits''
simultaneously on Broadway.
   The shows _ ``Cats,'' ``Starlight Express'' and ``The Phantom of
the Opera'' _ are all also running on the London stage.
   ``It is a wonderful honor for me as an English composer to be
honored by the American society,'' Lloyd Webber said.
   Lloyd Webber was accompanied to the Triple Play luncheon by his
wife, soprano Sarah Brightman, object of the Phantom's affection in
``The Phantom of the Opera.''
</TEXT>
