the International Association of Pathologists.
   _Tracy Goldsmith of Falmouth (Mass.) High School, whose study on
the water supply in her hometown has influenced local planning.
   _Jonathan Gross of Miami (Fla.) Killian High School, who has
studied the effects of amino acid on liver cancer at the University
of Miami.
   _Katrin Jellema of Grand Haven (Mich.) High School, who has
designed museum exhibits on mastadon bones from the ice age.
   _David Kaufman of Altoona (Pa.) Area High School, who has
developed an original algebraic formula.
   _Alice Kim of Pittsford-Mendon High School in Pittsford, N.Y., a
concert pianist who has performed with the Rochester Philarmonic.
   _John Miller of Salesianum School in Wilmington, Del., who has
done research for the National Weather Service on calibration of
visibility sensors.
   _Beth Noveck, of Lakewood Prep in Howell, N.J., who is teaching
Russian to her Chinese teacher and who also speaks French, German
and Hebrew.
   _Jennifer Patience of Thousand Oaks (Calif.) High School, who
invented a machine that translates computer text into Braille for
