<HEAD>Rep. Ted Weiss Hospitalized For Kidney Stone</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. Ted Weiss, D-N.Y., has been hospitalized
in New York City for treatment of a kidney stone, a spokesman said
here Monday.
   Weiss, 60, was in Columbia Presbyterian Hospital in Manhattan,
according to Michael Timmeny, the congressman's administrative
assistant.
   ``They're going to try to dissolve it,'' Timmeny said of the
kidney stone. ``When is he going to be out? When it's dissolved.''
   Timmeny said he had spoken by telephone to Weiss several times
since he entered the hospital late Friday and ``he says everything
is fine.''
   Weiss, who has a history of heart problems, underwent quadruple
bypass surgery in 1986 after he collapsed at a Capitol Hill
banquet. He also underwent single bypass heart surgery in 1982.
