<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail,</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Monday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   JESSE JACKSON, saying he deserves credit for registering ``more
Democrats than anybody else in history'' and continuing his appeal
for party fairness: ``We're not discussing generosity. We're
discussing reciprocity.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, answering Jackson's contention that he is being
treated unfairly: ``This is a campaign for delegates as well as
votes. We all knew what we were doing and what we were running
against.''
   
   PAT ROBERTSON, formally putting his presidential campaign on
hold to return to his faltering Christian Broadcasting System: ``I
suspend my candidacy ... but I do not now nor will I ever suspend
my advocacy of conservative and moral principles.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, stepping away from Reagan administration policies
on acid rain: ``With regard to acid rain, we can't study the
problem any more _ we've got to begin to take effective action.
There has to be a national commitment to continue to reduce the
emissions of sulfur and nitrogen oxides.''
