<HEAD>Two Construction Workers Killed in Fall From Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two construction workers were killed Monday
when they fell from the top of a 12-story downtown building.
   Francis Middlecamp, 57, of Baltimore, and Bruce Fahrenholtz, 29,
of Chesapeake Beach, Md. were doing sheet metal work on the
penthouse of the building about 8:15 a.m. when they fell into an
alley below.
   Three other men were working nearby but did not see what caused
the two to fall, said District of Columbia police Officer Shannon
Cockett.
   Nicholas Powe, who was hosing down the sidewalk of a neighboring
store, said one of the almost hit him.
   ``I couldn't do nothing for them,'' Powe said.
   The men worked for the James Myers Co. of Beltsville, Md.
   Police were investigating the accident.
