<HEAD>Adv22</HEAD>
<NOTE>For Release Sunday, May 22 and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>With BC-AP Arts: Rambo</HEAD>
<HEAD>The Rambo Saga in Brief</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<HEAD>``FIRST BLOOD''</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   John J. Rambo, a sullen former Green Beret, is hassled by a
small-town sheriff, then arrested for vagrancy. Rambo accepts
senseless beatings but _ amid flashbacks of torture in Vietnam _
decides a shave is just going too far. Punches out entire sheriff's
department, heads for the hills. Knocks out helicopter with rock,
killing two; routs sheriff's department, holds off National Guard.
   Rambo then blows up extensive portions of sheriff's town, wounds
sheriff, then surrenders to Col. Trautman, his former commanding
officer.
   
   Rambo sez: ``There are no friendly civilians, sir.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<HEAD>``RAMBO: FIRST BLOOD, PART II''</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Trautman apologizes to Rambo for having to serve hard time for
previous misunderstandings, offers chance to hunt for MIAs in
Vietnam. Rambo finds several and rescues one, annoying treacherous
Washington bureaucrat who peevishly orders a rescue helicopter to
strand Rambo in enemy territory.
   Rambo is tortured, but sadistic Soviet soldiers are no match for
Rambo and Co, his lovely Vietnamese helpmeet. They kill dozens, and
Rambo suffers a hand wound. A kiss, a burst of machine-gun fire,
and Co is dead.
   More fire and corpses. Rambo takes over helicopter in flight,
destroys prison camp, rescues MIAs, knocks out Soviet gunship,
returns to base in Thailand and attacks U.S. computers. Trautman
issues presidential pardon on the spot.
   
   Rambo sez: ``Do we get to win this time?''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<HEAD>``RAMBO III''</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Rambo takes up residence at a Buddhist monastery, helping patch
the roof and raising money by going off to town for the occasional
stickfight. Trautman asks him to join a mission in Afghanistan, but
Rambo says, ``My war is over.'' Until Trautman is captured. Rambo
to the rescue, assisted by one Afghani and a kid. Please, no
wagering.
   
   Trautman sez: ``We've already had our Vietnam. Now you're going
to get yours.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday, May 22</NOTE>
