<HEAD>London Stock Prices Fall</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: updates with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London Stock Exchange staged a late
afternoon about-face Monday, dropping as market makers trimmed
prices in the absence of new impetus to influence trading.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index closed down
5.2 points, or 0.29 percent, at 1776.2.
   Dealers said volume was light as traders awaited direction from
Tuesday's U.S. merchandise trade data for March. Economists
surveyed by Dow Jones expect the U.S. trade shortfall to have
narrowed to $12.6 billion from $13.8 billion in February.
   In addition, several British indicators expected this week were
keeping dealings cautious, most notably April's Public Sector
Borrowing Requirement on Wednesday and money supply data on
Thursday.
