<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Retail     05-16 0208</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Retail,0217</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>K mart Sales, Earnings Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TROY, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   K mart Corp. said Monday its earnings rose
4.6 percent during the first quarter, when sluggish sales took a
toll on the profits of most U.S. retailers.
   K mart reported net income of $120.8 million, or 60 cents a
share, for the quarter ended April 29, up from $115.5 million, or
57 cents a share, in the same period of 1987.
   The retailer reported sales of $5.84 billion, up from $5.59
billion.
   Sales on a comparable-store basis _ stores open both in the 1987
first quarter and the just-ended quarter _ rose 1.5 percent.
   ``Cooler-than-normal weather in April adversely affected sales
of outdoor patio goods and plants, both very important seasonal
lines for K mart, and also hurt sales of our apparel lines,''
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Joseph E. Antonini said in a
statement.
   ``Despite the difficult sales environment, we were able to
report higher earnings because of our tight cost control and a
lower effective tax rate,'' he said.
   K mart is the nation's second-largest retailer, behind Sears,
Roebuck & Co. As of April 27, K mart operated 2,224 K mart discount
stores, 1,153 Waldenbooks, 118 Builders Square and 253 Pay Less
Drug stores.
</TEXT>
