<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Rowntree     05-16 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Rowntree,0148</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nestle Confirms Further Purchases of Rowntree Shares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The giant Swiss food manufacturer Nestle SA said
Monday it was increasing its 14.7 percent stake in Rowntree PLC in
a continued effort to take over the British candy maker.
   Nestle said it purchased more Rowntree shares Friday and Monday.
   The Swiss company has offered to buy Rowntree for 2.1 billion
pounds, or $3.95 billion.
   Judging by the modest volume of trade, Nestle's total purchases
were small. According to official stock exchange figures, which
count both the buy and sell side of a transaction, 1.1 million
Rowntree shares changed hands.
   Nestle is also the object of a controversial takeover bid from
the Swiss company Jacobs Suchard, which has a 29.9 percent stake in
the company, the maximum allowed under British takeover regulations
short of a full takeover bid.
</TEXT>
