<1ST_LINE>r f AM-AlleghenyInternational     05-16 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Allegheny International,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Annual Shareholders Meeting Postponed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Allegheny International Inc. said Monday its
annual shareholders meeting, originally scheduled for Friday, has
been enjoined by order of federal bankruptcy court.
   Company officials said the court temporarily restrained the
meeting for 90 days from Friday. The court ruled the
Pittsburgh-based company may call the annual meeting after its
reorganization plan is submitted to shareholders and creditors, but
before they have voted on it.
   U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Pittsburgh issued its ruling Monday as
a result of a motion by the Official Committee of Unsecured
Creditors of Allegheny International.
   ``Allegheny International did not ask the court to postpone its
annual meeting. But now that it has been postponed, AI management
can continue the pursuit of its primary objectives of filing a plan
of reorganiation and to further strengthen our consumer products
businesses,'' said Allegheny International Chairman Oliver S.
Travers.
   Allegheny International's products include Sunbeam and Oster
consumer electronics.
</TEXT>
